# Contract Risk Analyzer – AI Service

##  Project Overview (Day 1 – Day 10)

This project is an AI-powered Contract Risk Analyzer that processes contract text and identifies potential legal risks using AI.

It was developed incrementally scovering backend setup, AI integration, caching, security, and performance optimization.

---

##  Tech Stack

- Python (Flask)
- Groq LLM (AI analysis)
- REST API
- In-memory caching (SHA256)
- OWASP ZAP (security testing)

---

##  Development Progress

###  Day 1–2: Project Setup
- Flask project structure created
- Basic API setup
- Folder organization (routes, services)

---

###  Day 3–4: Core API Development
- Implemented `/create` endpoint
- JSON request/response handling
- Basic contract input processing

---

###  Day 5–6: AI Integration
- Integrated Groq LLM
- Generated structured contract analysis
- Output fields:
  - title
  - summary
  - overview
  - key_items
  - recommendations

---

###  Day 7: Caching & Health Monitoring
- Added SHA256-based caching
- Introduced `/health` endpoint
- Initial metrics tracking

---

###  Day 8: Security Enhancements
- Added security headers:
  - X-Content-Type-Options
  - X-Frame-Options
  - Content-Security-Policy
- Prepared for OWASP ZAP scan

---

###  Day 9: AI Optimization (Part A & B)
- Optimized response time (<2s)
- Implemented fallback mechanism:
  - `{ "is_fallback": true }`
- Improved API response structure
- Added performance metrics:
  - avg_response_time
  - requests_tracked



###  Day 10: Finalization
- Code cleanup
- Documentation
- GitHub integration
- Final testing & validation



